modules.description: This module implements the WAMP (Web Application Messaging Protocol) specification in OCaml, providing functions to construct and deconstruct WAMP messages such as HELLO, PUBLISH, SUBSCRIBE, and EVENT. It works with data types representing message types, roles (like Subscriber and Publisher), and structured message components including dictionaries and lists. Concrete use cases include building clients that can publish messages, subscribe to topics, and handle real-time events in a WAMP-compliant messaging system.
